18#include "../ODRowReader.h"
19
20#include <array>
21#include <algorithm>
22
23namespace ZXing {
24namespace OneD {
25namespace RSS {
26
27using FinderCounters = std::array<int, 4>;
28
29class ReaderHelper
30{
31 static constexpr float MAX_AVG_VARIANCE = 0.2f;
32 static constexpr float MAX_INDIVIDUAL_VARIANCE = 0.45f;
33
34 static constexpr float MIN_FINDER_PATTERN_RATIO = 9.5f / 12.0f;
35 static constexpr float MAX_FINDER_PATTERN_RATIO = 12.5f / 14.0f;
36
37public:
38 template <typename C, typename P>
39 static int ParseFinderValue(const C& counters, const P& finderPatterns)
40 {
41 for (size_t value = 0; value < finderPatterns.size(); ++value) {
42 if (RowReader::PatternMatchVariance(counters, finderPatterns[value], MAX_INDIVIDUAL_VARIANCE) < MAX_AVG_VARIANCE) {
43 return static_cast<int>(value);
44 }
45 }
46 return -1;
47 }
48
49 static bool IsFinderPatternExtended( const FinderCounters& counters, bool reversed )
50 {
51 int sumA = counters[0] + counters[1];
52 int sumB = counters[2] + counters[3];
53 float sum = static_cast<float>(sumA + sumB);
54 float ratio = (reversed ? sumB : sumA) / sum;
55 if (ratio >= MIN_FINDER_PATTERN_RATIO && ratio <= MAX_FINDER_PATTERN_RATIO) {
56 // passes ratio test in spec, but see if the counts are unreasonable
57 auto minmax = std::minmax_element(counters.begin(), counters.end());
58 return *minmax.second < 10 * *minmax.first;
59 }
60 return false;
61 }
62
63 static bool IsFinderPattern( const FinderCounters& counters )
64 {
65 // Rhe RSS14 finder pattern is 5 counts long, the FINDER_PATTERNS array contains only the first 4
66 // of those. The 5th is '1' (same as the forth). The 4 counters passed here are 2nd to 5th.
67 // The first 2 of those 4 is 10 to 12 times as wide as both of the last two.
68 int a = counters[0] + counters[1];
69 int b = counters[2];
70 int c = counters[3];
71
72 return a > 8 * b && a < 14 * b && a > 8 * c && a < 14 * c;
73 }
74
75 static int GetRSSvalue(const std::array<int, 4>& widths, int maxWidth, bool noNarrow);
76};
77
78} // RSS
79} // OneD
80} // ZXing
